Confusion has trailed the health status of veteran actress, Sidikat Odukanwi, popularly known as Iyabo Oko after the family initially announced her death. The actress’ daughter, Bisi Aisha, had announced her mother’s passing on Instagram on Wednesday night. Also, a colleague, Actress Foluke Daramola-Salako, announced her death. Foluke wrote on her Instagram page: “and finally we lost her.. rip Iyabo Oko, we did our best but God knows best” Bisi Aisha said: “May ur soul Rest In Peace mummy” - Advertisement - But on Thursday morning, Aisha updated the post, saying her mother who was said to be dead, was alive.   ‘Ankara’ maker signs Fally Ipupa as brand ambassador     64th Grammy Awards postponed over COVID-19     Bobrisky begs billionaires to patronise his ‘market’   “She moved her hand after being confirmed dead three hours ago. God, we’ll forever praise your holy name,” she said. The 61-year-old actress has over the years battled with ill-health which caused her to take a long break from the movie scene. She was born on November 15, 1960, in Iwo Local Government Area of Osun State. She started acting as a teenager in 1973. Sidikat had stage names such as “Iyabo Oko” “Apoti Aje” Sisi Mama”. Last year, one of her daughters, Olamide, disclosed that her mother was diagnosed with ischemic stroke about five years ago but kept her health issues away from the public. Yoruba Nollywood stars including Foluke Daramola, Iyabo Ojo, Bolaji Amusan, Mercy Aigbe and Biodun Okeowo, others assisted financially in the past.